features: A half pound lighter than Maxlite 4, this lightweight 25 inch spinner maximizes your packing power and is the ideal checked bag for medium to long trips.

4 wheel spinners rotate 360 degree for a smooth roll. Lightweight, sturdy PowerScope handle stops at 38 inch and 42.5 inch features a patented contour grip with rubberized touch points for easy maneuvering. Unique bottom tray design increases durability.

Expands up to 2 inch to maximize packing capacity. Features low profile top, side and bottom carry handles, two exterior compartments, full length interior lid pocket, side accessory pocket and adjustable hold down straps for packing convenience.
H20 Guard protects the interior lining from moisture. Case Dimensions: 25 in x 18 in x 11 in, Overall Dimensions (includes wheels & carry handles): 27 in x 18.5 in x 11.5 in, Weight: 7.3 lbs.

Limited Lifetime Coverage plus trusted companion promise, which covers the cost of repair for damage from airline or other common carrier for 1 year. Applicable when purchased as new and after registration.
body.description: Lighten up with the Maxlite 5 25 inch Expandable Spinner, the lighter-weight, ultra-durable, soft-sided spinner suitcase in a checked baggage size designed to accommodate medium–length and longer trips. Enjoy an easy, comfortable glide thanks to the 2-position adjustable PowerScope Lite handle with patented Contour Grip and 4-wheel 360 degree rotating spinners, and stay organized with a convenient front pocket, full-length interior lid pocket, side accessory pocket and roomy interior with adjustable hold-down straps. A high-tensile-strength expandable zipper maximizes packing space for impressive flexibility. Backed by a new and expanded Trusted Traveler Promise—for worry-free warranty coverage from Travelpro.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good capacity, much sturdier than it looks, fits how you need it to fit
reviews.reviewText: A lightweight, well-balanced "one week" suitcase. Very good.I put mine through a LOT this year on two complex global itineraries. It doesn't show any damage of any kind, still rolls beautifully, and was never any source of frustration. It's amazingly light (empty).The tapered shape is very effective (if packed correctly) at making sure your suitcase with stacked carryon won't fall over. Like all spinner (quad wheel) designs, it takes a little extra effort on rough pavement or over large gaps. Not enough to be frustrating, but you have to pay attention to "jump" it across the gaps or it may get stuck.This is the largest size suitcase I consider "manageable":* It'll fit (all 4 wheels) on the step of every escalator I took it on (at least two dozen)* It'll fit properly in the Amtrak end-of-car luggage racks (both NEC Regional and Acela)* It'll fit (tight) between the facing seats on the New York LIRR* It fit in the cargo area of all types of small taxis around the world* It fit through the hatch and in the narrow back end of a seaplane without any theatrics.* And not so large that it'll lend itself to overpacking past the checked weight limitIf that wasn't enough, it also went through transfers, sorting, load&unload in all kinds of temperature extremes, long haul flights, big airports, dinky little airports, being checked & transferred a dozen times. Held up like a champ. Better than me, possibly.Other thoughts:I'd characterize this as week-long suitcase. But for solo travelers, if you're a low-maintenance or high-density packer, don't do much shopping, and have a carry-on also? Comfortably 9-14 days, verified personally.For a couple packing together it's probably less, 4-6 days?If you're not carrying breakables, I think this sort of nylon construction is "easier" to work with than a hardside. It has some flex and some ability to squish, the expansion zipper works well, it's easy to pack w/o any special techniques.I've used Traevelpro's other products, but this first maxlite piece has me already ordering another size.Highly Recommended.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars High quality luggage, light and sturday
reviews.reviewText: I was a bit hesitant to spend so much on a suitcase when there are many less expensive options. But I saw a lot of positive feedback from reviewers here and on other websites. I also had a recommendation from a friend who uses his for travel several times a year. It is incredibly LIGHTWEIGHT which I think is a critical aspect of any suitcase. You are going to load it up with your clothes, etc., thus it really helps if the luggage isn't on the heavy side to begin with. This model has four wheels and moves extremely easily in its upright position. It is expandable and has more than sufficient pockets and zipper compartments. I did not rate the durability factor since I have only used it a few times. Will update if it shows any signs of being less than durable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great bag for a short trips!!!
reviews.reviewText: A borrowed this bag from a friend for an emergency trip that came up. I was gone for 5 days and was able to pack everything I needed with ease once I expressed the bag. It was a breeze to carry this on the plane, perfect fit for the over head even expanded. The wheels are smooth, the handle is sturdy. The bag handle loops came in handy and were sturdy for ease for pulling in and out of places. The zippers are good quality. Outside pockets are roomy enough for all pocket items and then some when going thru security.Loved it so much I had to buy a bag of my own. Used it twice now and every experience has been just as good as the first. Great color selection too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 29, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Small lightweight, soft side
reviews.reviewText: This is replacing a hard side bag. Didn’t like the hard side. Haven’t used this yet but it feels lightweight. Has outside pockets which, of course the hard side does not have. the expandable part seems larger at one end due to slant of bag I guess. I haven’t used this yet, but it moves easily, seems sturdy and looks like it will have a good amount of room to pack, especially with the expandable part. it has lots of inner and outer pockets for organization. The zippers seem sturdy. Seems much smaller than the 21 inch Kensington, London fog bag. That was my favorite but the wheels were apparently damaged by the airline and now they don’t make it anymore. I am giving away the 21 in hard side bag I bought and took one trip with. I really don’t like hard side bags. I never had one before but I miss the outside pockets and the give that a soft side bag has. I haven’t used this yet, but I’m hoping it will last as long as my old Kensington London fog bag.! That lasted seven years before the airlines wrecked the wheels. The London fog bag was plaid. This bag is blue – very attractive. Plus, I found that the wheelchair people at the airport who kindly helped me get my bag at baggage claim did not understand what plaid was. So I’m going to take a picture of my bag so they will know what it looks like. Although a solid blue is easier to identify for those not familiar with patterns, and non-English speakers. Happy trails!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The best carry on out there
reviews.reviewText: My favorite part about this bag is how balanced it stay and how easily it moves! I have traveled on train, bus, and plane with this bag and it has yet to disappoint. It is the perfect size for a carry on, fits in every overhead bin I've ever used, and just looks nice. I LOVE THIS BAG. I cannot say it enough, if you are on the fence, get this bag and don't look back!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good maneuverable spinner
reviews.reviewText: Purchased this suitcase after much research and deliberation and have been very happy with it during the first trip I took it on to Costa Rica. Have been trying to learn the art of packing light, and this suitcase helps right off the bat by being extremely lightweight. Interior is roomy enough, but really appreciate the full length outer pocket and especially the short additional outer pocket for keeping small essential items very accessible. Maneuvers very smoothly on most surfaces. And I love the deep rich burgundy color. Look forward to adding more pieces from this collection!
